ganga/python/GangaRobot
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The individual actions in the Robot can now throw exceptions that decide how the Robot will continue

GangaRobotContinueError: 
------------------------
Issue a warning but continue with next action

GangaRobotBreakError:
---------------------
Issue a warning and start over from beginning if running in infinite loop. If no infinite loop, the
Robot will quit.

GangaRobotFatalError:
---------------------
The Robot will quit.


The default behaviour if any other exception is thrown is the same as GangaRobotFatalError but this
can be changed in the initialisation. See the ROBOT.INI file for an example.


